<h1>Refund Policy</h1>
<p class="legal-page__meta"><em>Last updated: April 9, 2026</em></p>
<p>Custom and decorated apparel and promo products from The Sole Provider are made to order. Our refund policy reflects that reality — and our commitment to making things right when we get it wrong.</p>
<h2>The Short Version</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Custom work is final.</strong> Once production starts, orders can't be cancelled, returned, or refunded.</li>
<li><strong>If the mistake was on our end, we fix it.</strong> Reprint, replace, refund — whatever fits the situation.</li>
<li><strong>Report issues within 5 business days of delivery</strong> so we can act on it.</li>
</ul>
<h2>What We Cover</h2>
<p>We're responsible for fixing things when <strong>we</strong> caused them:</p>
<ul>
<li>Print quality issues on a properly-supplied file</li>
<li>The wrong product shipped</li>
<li>Our typo on a finalized proof</li>
<li>Anything that doesn't match what you approved</li>
</ul>
<p>If any of that happens, tell us within <strong>5 business days of delivery</strong> and we'll make it right — customer's choice of reprint, replacement, or refund.</p>
<h2>What We Don't Cover</h2>
<p>We are <strong>not</strong> able to refund or replace for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Sizes you ordered that didn't fit your team</li>
<li>Art files you supplied that were low-resolution, wrong dimensions, or had errors we couldn't reasonably catch</li>
<li>Designs you insisted on after we flagged a concern (e.g., a logo too small to embroider cleanly)</li>
<li>Anything you approved on a proof</li>
</ul>
<p>Once you approve a proof, that approval is binding. We build exactly what you signed off on.</p>
<h2>Damaged or Missing Items</h2>
<p>Custom apparel runs sometimes have small imperfections. We accept up to <strong>1% of the order or 1 piece (whichever is greater)</strong> as standard production margin — we typically catch those before they ship.</p>
<p>Anything beyond that tolerance gets replaced or refunded at your choice. Report damage or shortages within <strong>5 business days of delivery</strong>.</p>
<h2>Lost or Damaged in Transit</h2>
<p>Carriers (UPS, FedEx, USPS, LaserShip) are responsible for loss or damage in transit. File a carrier claim and we'll help you track and reconcile where we can. If a delay impacts a time-sensitive event, we will refund the shipping charge in good faith.</p>
<h2>Cancellations</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Before proof approval (with our approval):</strong> A 25% cancellation fee applies to everything except shipping and tax (which are refunded in full).</li>
<li><strong>After proof approval:</strong> No cancellations, no refunds. Production has begun.</li>
<li><strong>Graphic design once work has started:</strong> Non-refundable. We will revise the design as many times as needed to get it right (within reason); we don't refund design time.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Return Shipping</h2>
<p>If a return is approved, buyer pays the return shipping unless the issue was on our end.</p>
<h2>How to Request a Refund or Replacement</h2>
<p>Email us within 5 business days of delivery with your order number and a description (with photos if relevant) of the issue:</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> solepdistributions@gmail.com <strong>Phone:</strong> (978) 844-6206</p>
<p>We'll respond quickly and work with you on the best path forward. Most issues get resolved with a single conversation.</p>
